The transformed sequence appears to shift the last 0 before a non-zero digit and the first 0 after the same non-zero digit to the outside. This pattern continues until all zeroes are outside the non-zero digits or in the center (if there were any to start with). Now, implement this pattern using Python:

def transform(sequence):
    sequence = list(sequence)

    for i, char in enumerate(sequence):
        if char != '0':
            sequence[i-1], sequence[i] = sequence[i], sequence[i-1]
            break
    for i in reversed(range(len(sequence))):
        if sequence[i] != '0':
            sequence[i+1], sequence[i] = sequence[i], sequence[i+1]
            break
    return ''.join(sequence)

